article_title: Supercut: The House Has Tried to Mess With Obamacare More Than 50 Times
article_text: Connecting decision makers to a dynamic network of information, people and ideas, Bloomberg quickly and accurately delivers business and financial information, news and insight around the world.

article_metadata.description: They just can't help themselves. On Tuesday, the House of Representatives voted 239-186 to repeal the 2010 Affordable Care Act, otherwise known as Obamacare. It was the 56th time House Republican lawmakers have voted to repeal or modify the law. Watch Congress members vote to mess with Obamacare again, and again, and again.
